  "texts": [
    "In recent years, transformer language models achieved major successes in German-focused NLP.",
    "Transformer language models usually implement one of three architectures: encoder, decoder, or the encoder-decoder, which combines the previous two (Vaswani et al., 2017).",
    "Encoders are usually aimed at providing vector representations of textual input.",
    "This makes them appropriate for text-, sentenceand token-level classification and regression tasks.",
    "Decoders are trained to predict the next token for a sequence of input tokens."
  ],
